                    <comment id="12474462" author="olegk" created="Tue, 20 Feb 2007 15:02:07 +0000"  >I think we ought not simply port the fix, but we should try to replace the notification mechanism based on Thread#interrupt() to that based on Object#wait() / Object#notify()&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg </comment>
                    <comment id="12474475" author="rolandw" created="Tue, 20 Feb 2007 15:34:23 +0000"  >So do I. But you urged me not to screw with the logic until we&amp;#39;ve got test coverage, and I&amp;#39;d like to keep it in sync with MTHCM until then.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
cheers,&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Roland&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12474605" author="mbecke" created="Tue, 20 Feb 2007 23:07:46 +0000"  >I would leave it with Thread.interrupt() for now.  Using object.wait() will be much more complicated and will require java.util.concurrent or an implementation of Mutex inside HttpConn.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Mike</comment>
